# Copy this file to ~/.config/dotfiles-autocommit.env (NOT into the dotfiles
# repo itself) and fill in real value(s), then:
#   chmod 600 ~/.config/dotfiles-autocommit.env
#
# bin/git-auto-sync.sh tries these in order, falling back to a timestamp-only
# commit message ("auto-sync: <date>") if a key is missing or the call fails:
#   1. QWEN_API_KEY      - self-hosted vLLM endpoint (inference.provocative.earth)
#   2. ANTHROPIC_API_KEY - Claude Haiku via the Anthropic API
# At least one should be set for a meaningful (non-fallback) commit message.

ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-your-key-here

# Optional - tried first if set. Get one from whoever administers
# inference.provocative.earth.
#QWEN_API_KEY=your-key-here
